            <entry xml:id="entry_faǵys" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>faǵys</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fagus</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>навоз</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>manure</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>(Syrdony) skʼaxtoj æmæ jæ faǵysy bænygædtoj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>(Сырдона) откопали и зарыли его в навоз</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Syrdon was dug up and buried in manure</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>I
                            176</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>x˳ymtæm faǵys lasæm</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>возим навоз на пашни</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q/>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ǧog ... xwallag nixxælew kænuj, fagusi xæccæ sxælæ-mulæ uj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>корова разбрасывает корм, (и он) перемешивается с навозом</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the cow is scattering the food so it is getting mixed with the
                                manure</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>II 19</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Xorany qal fyrt faǵysy raǧyl jæxī fækodta dywwadæs cæfy</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кичливый сын Хорана на навозной куче нанес себе двенадцать ран</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Khoran's puffy son inflicted twelve wounds on himself in a dung
                                heap</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."
                            /><biblScope>174</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Одно из старейших тюркских отложений в осетинском. Ср.
                        <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>baguš, bauguš, baguš</w>
                        <gloss><q>навоз</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="alt"><lang/>
                        <w>paǧai</w>
                        <gloss><q>поганый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="alt"
                            ><w>paǧaila</w>
                        <gloss><q>осквернять</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">IV 1132
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">IV 1132 ff.</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sah"><lang/>
                        <w>paхai, baǧas</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">междометие</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">interjection</note>
                        <gloss><q>мерзость!</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sah"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>гадость!</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sah"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>гадко!</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sah"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>скверно!</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sah"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>мерзко!</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cv"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">пака</w>
                        <gloss><q>пакость</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cv"
                            ><w n="0">пах</w>
                        <gloss><q>кал</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cv"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>навоз</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mn"><lang/>
                        <w>bāxa-</w>
                        <gloss><q>испражняться</q></gloss></mentioned> и др. По сообщению С. Е.
                    %sМалова%s, в языке желтых уйгуров существует глагольная основа <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ug"><lang/>
                        <w>paka-</w>
                        <gloss><q>испражняться</q></gloss></mentioned>, чем полностью подтверждается
                    тюркский характер рассматриваемого слова, представляющего отглагольное
                    образование. В осетинский слово проникло еще в ту эпоху, когда действовал закон
                    перехода %ip%i в %if%i, т. е. очень давно. Исходная форма, которую предполагает
                    ос. %ifagus%i, должна была звучать %i*pakuš%i. %bРусск.%b <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>пакость</w></mentioned>, если и не идет отсюда, все же в своей семантике
                    подверглось влиянию вышеприведенных (чувашского?) слов (ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">пакость</w>
                        <gloss><q>вред</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ущерб</q></gloss></mentioned>, но не ‘гадость’, ‘дерьмо’).</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">One of the oldest Turkic strata in Ossetic. Cf. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>baguš, bauguš, baguš</w>
                        <gloss><q>manure</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="alt"><lang/>
                        <w>paǧai</w>
                        <gloss><q>rotten</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="alt"
                            ><w>paǧaila</w>
                        <gloss><q>defile</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">IV 1132
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">IV 1132 ff.</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sah"><lang/>
                        <w>paхai, baǧas</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">междометие</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">interjection</note>
                        <gloss><q>nasty!</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sah"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>yuck!</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cv"><lang/>
                        <w>paka</w>
                        <gloss><q>mean trick</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cv"
                            ><w>pax</w>
                        <gloss><q>excrement</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cv"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>manure</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mn"><lang/>
                        <w>bāxa-</w>
                        <gloss><q>defecate</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. According to S. E.
                    %sMalov%s, there is a verbal stem <mentioned xml:lang="ug"><lang/>
                        <w>paka-</w>
                        <gloss><q>defecate</q></gloss></mentioned>, by which the Turkic nature of
                    the considered word (representinf a deverbal derivative) is fully confirmed. The
                    word entered Ossetic still in the era when the law of transition of %ip%i into
                    %if%i was in force, i. e. a long time ago. The initial form, which is suggested
                    by Ossetic %ifagus%i, should have sounded like %i*pakuš%i. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>пакость</w>
                        <gloss><q>mean trick</q></gloss></mentioned>, even if it does not come from
                    it, still was influenced in its semantics by the above mentioned (Chuvash?)
                    words (cf. <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>pakostь</w>
                        <gloss><q>harm</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>damage</q></gloss></mentioned>, but not ‘muck’, ‘shit’).</etym>
            </entry>
